  "prompt": "How do I custom-make my online wedding invitation?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to create a custom online wedding invitation:\n\n1. Choose a design platform\n- Canva\n- Paperless Post\n- Greenvelope\n- Minted\n- Wedding Wire\n\n2. Select a template or start from scratch\n- Pick a style matching your wedding theme\n- Choose colors matching your wedding palette\n- Consider your wedding's aesthetic (formal, rustic, modern)\n\n3. Personalize the design\n- Add your names\n- Include wedding date and time\n- Specify venue location\n- Add RSVP options\n- Insert wedding website link (if applicable)\n\n4. Customize graphics and fonts\n- Upload personal photos\n- Choose complementary fonts\n- Add decorative elements\n- Adjust layouts\n\n5. Review and proofread\n- Check all details for accuracy\n- Have someone else review\n- Test digital invitation on multiple devices\n\n6. Select distribution method\n- Email invitations\n- Social media sharing\n- Wedding website integration\n- Digital invitation platforms\n\n7. Optional extras\n- Track RSVPs\n- Send digital save-the-dates\n- Include additional wedding information\n- Create digital guest list management\n\nPrices range from free to $2-$5 per invitation, depending on platform and features.",
